      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "d1888b41-2782-44bc-8b77-e5c39e3d4e87",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#030803 0%,#061206 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Step 3 — Custom Networks (Optional)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "Two network profiles are available depending on your lab needs. You can define one or both.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "",
      "codeLang": "",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": false,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
    {
      "id": "763749cc-00aa-494d-a97a-6f7599373747",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#030803 0%,#061206 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option A — NAT (NAT)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "VMs get a private internal network. Internet access is routed through the host via NAT.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo vim /tmp/NAT.xml",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
    {
      "id": "f53298ee-4d6b-4a86-9b4b-5445d4cfa9ef",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option A — NAT (NAT)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [
        "Setting  ::  Value",
        "Network name  ::  NAT",
        "Bridge interface  ::  virbr10",
        "Internal domain  ::  shadow_lab",
        "Gateway  ::  10.10.10.1",
        "DHCP range  ::  10.10.10.2 – 10.10.10.200"
      ],
      "codeText": "<network>\n  <name>NAT</name>\n  <forward mode='nat'/>\n  <bridge name='virbr10' stp='on' delay='0'/>\n  <domain name='shadow_lab'/>\n  <ip address='10.10.10.1' netmask='255.255.255.0'>\n    <dhcp>\n      <range start='10.10.10.2' end='10.10.10.200'/>\n    </dhcp>\n  </ip>\n</network>",
      "codeLang": "xml",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": true,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "bb7a0c6d-1b52-41e9-b670-81e0e41201d2",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option A — NAT (NAT)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo virsh net-define /tmp/NAT.xml\nsudo virsh net-start NAT\nsudo virsh net-autostart NAT",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "87a3cf7f-37d6-4a62-9e0e-e654c8c4ee0f",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#030803 0%,#061206 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option B — Bridged LAN (LAN)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "Replace eth0 with your actual host interface (ip link to check).",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "VMs attach directly to the physical LAN via an unmanaged switch. No DHCP is available on the network — every VM needs a static IP configured inside the guest OS.\nReserved IP range for QEMU VMs: 172.16.0.15 – 172.16.0.19\nFirst, bridge the physical interface on the host:\nTo persist across reboots, add the bridge to your network manager config (e.g. systemd-networkd or NetworkManager).\nThen define the libvirt network:",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo ip link add virbr20 type bridge\nsudo ip link set eth0 master virbr20\nsudo ip link set virbr20 up",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": true,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
    {
      "id": "626bbe75-0dc5-4bb0-b5fe-c6703523f401",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option B — Bridged LAN (LAN)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo vim /tmp/LAN.xml",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "43a92e53-164c-4a64-b4c1-ba9ce9732440",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option B — Bridged LAN (LAN)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [
        "Setting  ::  Value",
        "Network name  ::  LAN",
        "Bridge interface  ::  virbr20",
        "Reserved range  ::  172.16.0.15 – 172.16.0.19",
        "Gateway  ::  set on your router/host"
      ],
      "codeText": "<network>\n  <name>LAN</name>\n  <forward mode='bridge'/>\n  <bridge name='virbr20'/>\n</network>",
      "codeLang": "xml",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": true,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "3f9eb8de-008d-4688-8b0b-381fe398397a",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option B — Bridged LAN (LAN)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "#### Setting a Static IP Inside a VM\nAfter creating a VM on the LAN network, configure the static IP inside the guest. Using nmcli:",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo virsh net-define /tmp/LAN.xml\nsudo virsh net-start LAN\nsudo virsh net-autostart LAN",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "b2237793-eba2-4f06-9461-a42189645be3",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#020602 0%,#040d04 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Option B — Bridged LAN (LAN)",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 48,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "Increment the last octet (172.16.0.15, .16, .17…) for each new VM. Keep a note of which IP is assigned to which VM to avoid conflicts within the reserved range.",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "# Run inside the VM guest\nnmcli con mod \"Wired connection 1\" \\\n  ipv4.method manual \\\n  ipv4.addresses 172.16.0.15/24 \\\n  ipv4.gateway 172.16.0.1 \\\n  ipv4.dns \"1.1.1.1 8.8.8.8\"\nnmcli con up \"Wired connection 1\"",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": true,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
      "id": "effe446a-db12-4ebd-9a7b-dc2a5686bcc5",
      "layout": "top",
      "bgType": "gradient",
      "bgColor": "#080b08",
      "bgGradient": "linear-gradient(160deg,#030803 0%,#061206 100%)",
      "bgImage": "",
      "titleText": "Verify",
      "titleColor": "#00ff41",
      "titleSize": 36,
      "subtitleText": "",
      "subtitleColor": "#2a6b3a",
      "bodyText": "",
      "bodyColor": "#7ab87a",
      "bodySize": 22,
      "bullets": [],
      "codeText": "sudo virsh net-list --all\nsudo virsh net-info NAT\nsudo virsh net-info LAN",
      "codeLang": "bash",
      "imageUrl": "",
      "showTitle": true,
      "showSubtitle": false,
      "showBody": false,
      "showBullets": false,
      "showCode": true,
      "showImage": false,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "fontFamily": "'Courier New', 'Fira Mono', monospace",
      "transition": "slide-r"
    },
